<% content_for :titolo, "#{@pagina.titolo} - #{@pagina.numero}" %>

<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-3 md:p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 text-black dark:text-white font-mono transition-colors duration-300"
     data-controller="exercise-checker page-viewer fill-blanks auto-advance text-toggle font-controls"
     data-page-viewer-image-url-value="<%= asset_path('bus3_mat/p107/page.png') %>"
     data-text-toggle-target="content"
     data-font-controls-target="content">

  <!-- Header -->
  <%= render 'shared/page_header', pagina: @pagina %>

  <!-- Esercizio 1 -->
  <div class="bg-[#C7EAFB] dark:bg-cyan-900/40 p-4 md:p-6 -mx-3 md:mx-0 mb-12">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="bg-red-500 text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold flex-shrink-0">1</div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200"><strong>Leggi e osserva la tabella.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4">L'unità di misura fondamentale di lunghezza è il <strong class="text-cyan-500">metro</strong>. Il suo simbolo è <strong class="text-cyan-500">m</strong>.</p>
    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mb-4">
      <li>Per misurare <strong>lunghezze superiori al metro</strong>, come la distanza tra due città o l'altezza di una torre, si usano i <strong class="text-pink-500">multipli</strong> del metro.</li>
      <li>Per misurare <strong>lunghezze inferiori al metro</strong>, come quelle di piccoli oggetti, si usano i <strong class="text-green-500">sottomultipli</strong> del metro.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Tabella misure -->
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-center">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th colspan="3" class="bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/30 text-pink-500 p-2 border font-bold">MULTIPLI</th>
            <th class="bg-cyan-100 dark:bg-cyan-900/40 text-cyan-600 p-2 border font-bold">UNITÀ<br>FONDAMENTALE</th>
            <th colspan="3" class="bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-500 p-2 border font-bold">SOTTOMULTIPLI</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-pink-500 border"><span>CHILOMETRO</span><br><span class="text-pink-500">km</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-pink-500 border"><span>ETTOMETRO</span><br><span class="text-pink-500">hm</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-pink-500 border"><span>DECAMETRO</span><br><span class="text-pink-500">dam</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-cyan-500 border"><span>METRO</span><br><span>m</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-green-500 border"><span>DECIMETRO</span><br><span class="text-green-500">dm</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-green-500 border"><span>CENTIMETRO</span><br><span class="text-green-500">cm</span></th>
            <th class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 p-2 text-green-500 border"><span>MILLIMETRO</span><br><span class="text-green-500">mm</span></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">1000 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">100 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">10 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">1 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">0,1 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">0,01 m</td>
            <td class="p-2 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border">0,001 m</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-4 border-purple-400 dark:border-purple-500 rounded-lg p-3 mt-4 text-center">
      <p>Ogni misura è <strong class="text-pink-500">10 volte minore</strong> di quella alla sua sinistra e <strong class="text-pink-500">10 volte maggiore</strong> di quella alla sua destra.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Esercizio 2 -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4">
      <div class="bg-red-500 text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold flex-shrink-0">2</div>
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200"><strong>Osserva il righello e completa.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
      <div class="dark:bg-white rounded-xl p-2 inline-block"><%= image_tag "bus3_mat/p107/p107_01.jpg", alt: "Righello con misure", class: "max-w-xl w-full rounded-lg" %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p>• In 1 metro ci sono 10 decimetri. → 1 m = 10 dm → 1 dm è <sup>1</sup>/<sub>10</sub> del metro</p>
      <p>• In 1 decimetro ci sono <input type="text" data-fill-blanks-target="input" data-correct-answer="10" class="w-16 px-2 py-1 border-b-2 border-dotted border-gray-400 dark:border-gray-500 bg-transparent dark:text-white text-center"> centimetri. → 1 dm = 10 cm</p>
      <p class="ml-4">In 1 metro ci sono 10 dm, quindi 100 cm. → 1 m = 100 cm → 1 cm è <sup>1</sup>/<sub>100</sub> del metro</p>
      <p>• In 1 centimetro ci sono <input type="text" data-fill-blanks-target="input" data-correct-answer="10" class="w-16 px-2 py-1 border-b-2 border-dotted border-gray-400 dark:border-gray-500 bg-transparent dark:text-white text-center"> millimetri. → 1 cm = 10 mm</p>
      <p class="ml-4">In 1 metro ci sono 100 cm, quindi 1000 mm. → 1 m = 1000 mm → 1 mm è <sup>1</sup>/<sub>1000</sub> del metro</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Quaderno -->
  <div class="p-4 mb-8 text-right">
    <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Quaderno →</span> <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">p. 167</span>
  </div>

  <%= render 'shared/exercise_controls' %>
</div>
